-- Ukraine’s Five-Month State Budget Gap Widens, Ministry Says
-- B y   D a r y n a   K r a s n o l u t s k a
-- 2012-06-26T08:55:13Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-26/ukraine-s-five-month-state-budget-gap-widens-ministry-says.html
Ukraine’s state budget deficit
widened in the first five months of the year from the same
period a year ago as spending rose, the  Finance Ministry  said.  The shortfall totaled 3.66 billion hryvnia ($453 million),
compared with 1.58 billion hryvnia a year earlier, the ministry,
based in Kiev, said today in a statement on its  website .
Spending increased to 135.6 billion hryvnia in the period from
119.6 billion a year ago, the ministry said.  Ukraine raised 5.1 billion hryvnia from state-asset sales
in January-May, according to the statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
